# Copy to .sandcastle/.env and fill in. This file is gitignored.

# --- Claude (the agent) ---
# Use your Claude subscription: run `claude setup-token` and paste the result.
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
# ...or an API key instead (uncomment):
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Forge identity: IMPLEMENTER (dev-agent) ---
# GitHub: a fine-grained PAT (Contents RW, Pull requests RW, Issues RW, Metadata R)
#         for a bot account that is a write collaborator.
GH_TOKEN=
# GitLab: a project/personal access token (api, write_repository) for the dev bot.
# GITLAB_TOKEN=
# Self-hosted GitLab ONLY: the instance host (e.g. gitlab.example.net). Injected into the
# sandbox so `glab` can resolve a non-gitlab.com remote. gitlab.com users leave this unset.
# GITLAB_HOST=

# --- Forge identity: REVIEWER ---
# The reviewer credential does NOT go here. Every key in this file is injected into EVERY
# agent sandbox, so a FORGE_REVIEW_TOKEN here would let the implementer approve its own PR.
# Put it in .sandcastle/.env.review instead (host-only). See .sandcastle/.env.review.example.
# The loop refuses to start if FORGE_REVIEW_TOKEN is set here.

# Set automatically from afk.config.json by the runners; only override to force it.
# FORGE_PLATFORM=github

# --- Concurrent loops (optional) ---
# Run N loops over one backlog (e.g. two clones on this machine) without collisions:
# give each clone a unique LOOP_ID. A loop claims an issue on pickup with the label
# `working:<LOOP_ID>` and only drives its own PRs. Lowest id wins a simultaneous claim;
# stagger the loops' start by ~30–60s to make races rare. Inspect with `pnpm afk:claims`.
# UNSET = today's single-loop behavior (no claims, owns everything). Loaded on the HOST.
# LOOP_ID=a
